# https://stackoverflow.com/a/51429852/4156752
# Whitelist pattern: ignore everything, then re-allow what the Docker build
# actually needs. Keeps the build context small + deterministic — stray
# local files, caches, secrets in gitignored folders can't leak into the image.

# Ignore everything
*

# Allow source + config read by `pnpm install` and `pnpm run build`
!/.docker
!/app
!/bin
!/content
!/public
!/package.json
!/pnpm-lock.yaml
!/pnpm-workspace.yaml
!/flake.nix
!/flake.lock
!/react-router.config.ts
!/tsconfig.json
!/vite.config.ts

# Re-ignore noise that could sneak in through the allowed directories
**/node_modules
**/.DS_Store
**/Thumbs.db
**/*.log
**/*~
